== Romanian ==
=== Etymology ===
From [[W:Proto-Indo-European language|PIE]] ''*mend-'', "horse", via a pre-Roman language. It is unanimously agreed to be [[cognate]] to the [[W:Thracian language|Thracian]] word ''mezenai'', "horse", and [[W:Messapian language|Messapian]] ''Menzana'', a horse deity.
There is also an Albanian cognate, ''mëz''.

===Noun===
'''mânz'''
#[[colt]], young horse.

